  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b8e\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bca\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b9a\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b87\u0b9f\u0bae\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc6\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bb0\u0ba3\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0bae\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0bb5\u0bb2\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb4\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bc6\u0baf\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0bae\u0bc7\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bca\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb3\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0baa\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bca\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd - \u0ba4\u0bc1\u0bb7\u0bbe\u0bb0 \u0b87\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0ba9\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Deaths in fuel queues are massacres to debilitate people - Dushara Indus",
      "author": "Vishnu",
      "body_lines": [
        "Everyone expected that when President Gotabaya Rajapaksa visited the Parliament on Tuesday 5th, he would say something good about the current situation of the country.",
        "But he did not come for that. On the contrary, according to the constitution, his intention was to visit the parliament once in three months and protect his profession, United People's Power Member of Parliament Tushara Indunil pointed out.",
        "Instead, they are killed by making them wait in queues for long periods of time, physically and psychologically weakening them.",
        "What is the compensation for these deaths and the affected families? He also questioned.",
        "He said the above while participating in a press conference organized yesterday (6) at the office of the Leader of the Opposition in Colombo. There he added:",
        "The then Minister Richard Patherana expressed strong opposition to President Premadasa when he visited the Parliament while the charge sheet was being brought against former President R. Premadasa.",
        "However, even in that extraordinary situation, President R. Premadasa addressed Parliament with great courage and left.",
        "The President's visit to Parliament is a special occasion. It is also mentioned in the constitution that the President should visit the Parliament at least once in three months.",
        "So when President Gotabaya Rajapaksa visited Parliament the day before yesterday, everyone expected that he would say something good about the current situation of the country.",
        "But he did not come for that, simply 'I am still here.' We think that he has come to show that he has not run away anywhere.",
        "As per the constitution, he has to visit the parliament once in three months and he has come to the parliament the day before yesterday to protect his business.",
        "In the current situation, it is impossible to tell what will happen to President Gotabaya Rajapaksa if he walks alone on Rajapaksa Road or gets off near any petrol station.",
        "The people who had voted for Gotabaya Rajapaksa all over the country expressed their opposition by taking to the streets and fighting against him. But now there is opposition to him in the Parliament too. When will he understand the hostility of the Constitution against the executive?",
        "14th death reported on 05th in queue for fuel. It's not just deaths. Instead, they are killed by making them wait in queues for long periods of time, physically and psychologically weakening them. What is the compensation for these deaths and the affected families? He questioned."
      ],
